# Global Cursor Rules for Intelligent Signal Fusion System

## Language Requirements
- **ALL code and comments MUST be written in English**, regardless of the language used in user queries or conversations.
- Variable names, function names, class names, and all identifiers must use English.
- All comments, docstrings, and documentation strings must be in English.
- Error messages and log messages should be in English.
- This rule applies to all files in the project, including but not limited to:
  - Python source files (.py)
  - Configuration files (.yaml, .yml, .json, etc.)
  - Documentation files (.md)
  - Test files
  - Any other code or text files

## Code Style
- Follow PEP 8 style guidelines for Python code.
- Use descriptive English names for all variables, functions, and classes.
- Write clear, concise English comments explaining complex logic.

## Enforcement
- When editing or creating any file, ensure all code and comments are in English.
- If a user requests code in another language, still provide English code and comments, but you may explain in the requested language if needed.

